There's gonna be opportunities that are presented to me,

00:33:15.839 --> 00:33:18.199
opportunities that are presented to you

00:33:18.199 --> 00:33:20.139
and this is the embracing of the promise

00:33:20.179 --> 00:33:22.499
because he says, as we have therefore opportunity,

00:33:22.499 --> 00:33:26.419
notice, let us do good.

00:33:26.419 --> 00:33:27.979
So in verse number nine, he said,

00:33:27.979 --> 00:33:31.459
let us not be weary in well-doing

00:33:31.459 --> 00:33:33.979
and so we find that he then says in verse number 10,

00:33:33.979 --> 00:33:36.099
as we have therefore opportunity,

00:33:36.099 --> 00:33:41.099
let us do good unto all men,

00:33:41.479 --> 00:33:46.479
especially unto them who are the household of faith,

00:33:47.219 --> 00:33:49.779
those who are brothers and sisters in Christ

00:33:50.339 --> 00:33:54.419
and we see this, the contextual impact

00:33:54.419 --> 00:33:57.579
and really connection between verse nine with well-doing

00:33:57.579 --> 00:33:59.719
and verse 10 with do good.

00:34:01.919 --> 00:34:05.499
Again, it's not so that you can stay saved.

00:34:05.499 --> 00:34:08.299
I'm thankful, listen, my salvation is secure.

00:34:09.899 --> 00:34:12.319
It's as secure as it's ever gonna be

00:34:12.319 --> 00:34:15.859
because I'm in the hand of the Lord Jesus Christ

00:34:15.859 --> 00:34:18.979
and his hand is in the hand of the Father, amen?

00:34:18.979 --> 00:34:21.419
I have reserved in heaven for me an inheritance

00:34:21.419 --> 00:34:23.299
that is incorruptible and undefiled,

00:34:23.299 --> 00:34:26.459
it fadeth not away, hallelujah, man.

00:34:26.459 --> 00:34:27.779
Praise God.

00:34:27.779 --> 00:34:29.739
I talked to a man yesterday,

00:34:29.739 --> 00:34:32.179
down there in the Eastern Market

00:34:32.179 --> 00:34:34.179
and man, he was a religious man.

00:34:34.179 --> 00:34:37.259
I mean, super, super, super religious studying.

00:34:37.259 --> 00:34:39.819
I mean, he was degrees and all sorts of things

00:34:39.819 --> 00:34:40.819
and he was selling me some stuff

00:34:40.819 --> 00:34:42.459
and I said, so let me ask you this.

00:34:42.459 --> 00:34:45.619
Are you 100% sure if you're to die today, you go to heaven?

00:34:45.619 --> 00:34:47.179
Oh no, you can't know that.

00:34:49.339 --> 00:34:50.339
I said, really?

00:34:51.619 --> 00:34:53.459
Why isn't that?

00:34:53.459 --> 00:34:54.739
Shared some things with me and I said,

00:34:54.739 --> 00:34:57.559
well, I'm sure you're familiar with Paul.

00:34:57.559 --> 00:34:59.019
I referenced some things about Paul

00:34:59.019 --> 00:35:02.739
and how Paul shares with us and through the scriptures,

00:35:02.739 --> 00:35:07.739
his confidence of being with Jesus, hallelujah.

00:35:07.940 --> 00:35:10.739
I'm thankful this morning that our salvation is settled

00:35:12.299 --> 00:35:15.059
but God wants us to do good.

00:35:15.059 --> 00:35:17.339
He wants us to do these, as he says,

00:35:18.259 --> 00:35:21.459
not be weary in well-doing and he says, let us do good.

00:35:21.459 --> 00:35:26.159
Do these, carry out the work of the ministry.

00:35:26.159 --> 00:35:28.619
Carry out the work of the ministry.

00:35:28.619 --> 00:35:31.500
And as we begin to think about the context

00:35:31.500 --> 00:35:33.299
of all that's taking place here

00:35:33.299 --> 00:35:36.639
and I understand that we're living in this day

00:35:36.639 --> 00:35:40.479
and we have, yes, rejections and whatever happens

00:35:40.479 --> 00:35:43.059
but we must embrace the promise to know

00:35:43.059 --> 00:35:47.500
that God is doing something, that God is working

00:35:47.500 --> 00:35:49.419
and I'm gonna just trust him.

00:35:49.419 --> 00:35:51.339
I'm gonna embrace the promise.

00:35:51.339 --> 00:35:53.919
I'm not gonna just look for results.

00:35:54.940 --> 00:35:57.059
We live in a society

00:35:57.059 --> 00:35:59.859
that not only promotes instant gratification

00:35:59.859 --> 00:36:03.619
but we live in a society that is all about results.

00:36:03.619 --> 00:36:06.220
It is a results-driven society.

00:36:06.220 --> 00:36:07.940
What have you done for me lately?

00:36:09.119 --> 00:36:09.959
Amen?

00:36:10.959 --> 00:36:14.379
Professional sports teams, coaches get fired all the time

00:36:14.379 --> 00:36:16.559
because they didn't bring home a trophy.

00:36:16.559 --> 00:36:18.559
There was no championship that they brought home.

00:36:18.559 --> 00:36:19.919
By the way, there's one

00:36:19.919 --> 00:36:22.479
that gets the championship every year

00:36:22.479 --> 00:36:24.959
and there's however many else that don't get it.

00:36:24.959 --> 00:36:26.279
You know what I'm saying?

00:36:26.279 --> 00:36:31.199
But it's about that results-driven society that we live in.

00:36:31.199 --> 00:36:33.119
You look at corporations

00:36:33.119 --> 00:36:35.799
and I worked in the corporate world for years

00:36:35.799 --> 00:36:38.039
and it was all about metrics and metrics

00:36:38.039 --> 00:36:40.239
and what are your numbers and what are your metrics

00:36:40.239 --> 00:36:44.519
and what are you producing and what are your, I get it.

00:36:45.799 --> 00:36:49.699
We live in a society that will inflate things

00:36:49.699 --> 00:36:52.559
in order to show some type of results

00:36:52.559 --> 00:36:54.799
because that's what people want.

00:36:55.839 --> 00:36:59.459
But I can't produce results and neither can you.

00:37:01.779 --> 00:37:05.199
The question is not how many people got saved,

00:37:05.199 --> 00:37:07.500
the question is how much seed was sown.

00:37:08.359 --> 00:37:09.720
Amen?

00:37:09.720 --> 00:37:14.720
Because the Bible says that some plant, some water,

00:37:16.199 --> 00:37:19.539
but God gives the increase.

00:37:20.919 --> 00:37:25.919
I cannot, you cannot make somebody get saved.

00:37:30.379 --> 00:37:31.839
But you can sow the seed.

00:37:33.119 --> 00:37:35.039
You can water.

00:37:35.039 --> 00:37:36.619
You can be involved in that process

00:37:36.619 --> 00:37:40.000
and you can see God do what only God can do.

00:37:41.579 --> 00:37:44.339
See, God knows our frame.

00:37:44.339 --> 00:37:45.899
He knows we're frail.

00:37:45.899 --> 00:37:47.379
He knows we're but dust.

00:37:48.679 --> 00:37:50.819
And he knows that there's a potential,

00:37:50.819 --> 00:37:55.039
the danger of growing weary in well-doing.

00:37:55.940 --> 00:37:59.220
As we read not only here in Galatians but over there

00:37:59.220 --> 00:38:03.940
in the passage that we saw in 2 Thessalonians,

00:38:03.940 --> 00:38:07.500
he makes it abundantly clear that he says this,

00:38:07.500 --> 00:38:10.059
be not weary in well-doing.

00:38:11.179 --> 00:38:13.739
So the context again is all with regard

00:38:13.739 --> 00:38:15.739
to doing the work of the ministry.

00:38:16.659 --> 00:38:21.579
Maybe this morning you're a little bit discouraged

00:38:21.579 --> 00:38:24.419
because you don't see the results that you'd like to see.

00:38:25.599 --> 00:38:28.779
Maybe you get to the point, you say does it even matter?

00:38:28.779 --> 00:38:29.899
Do they even listen?

00:38:31.059 --> 00:38:32.539
No one even cares.

00:38:33.539 --> 00:38:35.299
Can I tell you this morning,

00:38:35.299 --> 00:38:38.940
let us not be weary in well-doing.

00:38:39.859 --> 00:38:42.399
Let us embrace the promise.

00:38:42.399 --> 00:38:45.820
Let us receive God's grace and God's mercy.

00:38:45.820 --> 00:38:47.119
Let us focus on the one.

00:38:47.119 --> 00:38:49.459
Listen, I'm not doing it for the results,

00:38:49.459 --> 00:38:50.820
I'm doing it for God.

00:38:52.820 --> 00:38:56.500
What a privilege to be a servant of the Lord.

00:38:56.500 --> 00:39:00.080
What a privilege to be engaged in the work of the ministry.

00:39:00.080 --> 00:39:02.039
See, we understand the work of the ministry

00:39:02.559 --> 00:39:04.080
is not just for the pastor.

00:39:04.080 --> 00:39:05.959
We understand Ephesians chapter number four,

00:39:05.959 --> 00:39:08.200
that the pastor is given to the church,

00:39:08.200 --> 00:39:11.039
is a gift to the church in order to equip the saints

00:39:11.039 --> 00:39:12.959
for the work of the ministry.

00:39:14.279 --> 00:39:17.200
And it's altogether possible that the individual

00:39:17.200 --> 00:39:20.959
that's serving as the pastor could grow weary in well-doing,

00:39:20.959 --> 00:39:23.200
but it's also possible that the congregants,

00:39:23.200 --> 00:39:25.839
the members of a local church

00:39:25.839 --> 00:39:28.679
can grow weary in well-doing.

00:39:28.679 --> 00:39:30.019
It's of interest to me.

00:39:30.019 --> 00:39:33.299
Listen, there are pastoral epistles in the New Testament.

00:39:34.219 --> 00:39:35.859
First, second, Timothy, Titus, right?

00:39:35.859 --> 00:39:38.339
Pastoral epistles, but then there's church epistles.

00:39:38.339 --> 00:39:41.940
Do you notice that the instruction of not growing weary

00:39:41.940 --> 00:39:44.339
is not written to Timothy and to Titus?

00:39:46.179 --> 00:39:47.839
It's written to churches.

00:39:49.059 --> 00:39:50.779
The churches in the region of Galatia

00:39:50.779 --> 00:39:52.380
and the church in Thessalonica.

00:39:53.219 --> 00:39:55.299
That should encourage us

00:39:55.299 --> 00:39:58.739
because we're all engaged in the work of the ministry.

00:39:58.739 --> 00:40:01.419
And God says, let us not.

00:40:01.419 --> 00:40:05.019
Let us not be weary in well-doing.

00:40:05.019 --> 00:40:06.739
Can I encourage you this morning?

00:40:06.739 --> 00:40:07.739
God's working.

00:40:07.739 --> 00:40:11.699
I don't know all that God's doing, but I know God's working.

00:40:11.699 --> 00:40:14.699
And I know that he's not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to

00:40:14.699 --> 00:40:15.699
repentance.

00:40:15.699 --> 00:40:17.699
Listen, I'd like to see more people saved.

00:40:17.699 --> 00:40:19.699
I'd like to see more people walk the aisle.

00:40:19.699 --> 00:40:20.779
I understand.

00:40:20.779 --> 00:40:24.659
Sometimes we get our focus on that, and sometimes we get our focus on that instead of the Lord.

00:40:24.659 --> 00:40:29.899
You know exactly what happens is we fall in that pitfall.

00:40:29.899 --> 00:40:30.899
We get weary.

00:40:30.899 --> 00:40:33.099
Because we're looking at the results.

00:40:33.099 --> 00:40:37.459
And God says, just get your eyes on me, looking unto Jesus, the author and finisher of our

00:40:37.459 --> 00:40:38.659
faith.

00:40:38.659 --> 00:40:42.579
This morning, there is a danger to acknowledge.

00:40:42.579 --> 00:40:46.099
There's the danger of growing weary, and I want to encourage you this morning.

00:40:46.099 --> 00:40:48.739
Keep on sowing to the Spirit.

00:40:48.739 --> 00:40:51.259
Keep on sowing the good seed.

00:40:51.259 --> 00:40:57.539
Because he says that in due season, we shall reap if we faint not.

00:40:57.539 --> 00:41:03.659
Help us to embrace that, and to trust the Lord to do what only he can do.

00:41:03.659 --> 00:41:04.659
Let us pray.

00:41:04.659 --> 00:41:05.979
Father, we love you.

00:41:05.979 --> 00:41:07.939
We thank you so much for loving us.

00:41:07.939 --> 00:41:11.339
We thank you for the privilege of being able to be your servants.

00:41:11.339 --> 00:41:16.299
We thank you that you've given us a Bible, and you've given us with clarity the dangers

00:41:16.299 --> 00:41:18.539
that we are faced with.

00:41:18.539 --> 00:41:23.739
And God, I pray that as your people, that you would help us to not grow weary in well-doing.

00:41:24.459 --> 00:41:26.299
Lord, help us to trust you.

00:41:26.299 --> 00:41:29.979
Help us, Lord, to receive the grace and the mercy that we need.

00:41:29.979 --> 00:41:35.219
Lord, help us, I pray, to keep on keeping on.

00:41:35.219 --> 00:41:37.299
Help us to faint not.

00:41:37.299 --> 00:41:40.259
I pray that you'd work in hearts and lives as only you can.

00:41:40.259 --> 00:41:43.699
I pray that your name alone would be glorified through every decision that is made.

00:41:43.699 --> 00:41:45.619
For it's in Christ's name we pray.

00:41:45.619 --> 00:41:46.339
Would you stand with me?

